  "title": "Healthcare/Clinic Typist",
  "description": "<p>Job Description</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>-Listen to the recorded dictation of doctors.</p><p>-Transcribe and interpret the dictation into diagnostic test results and reports.</p><p>-Make sure the transcription is correct, complete and has a consistent style.</p><p>-Identify inconsistencies, error and missing information within a report that could compromise patient care.</p><p>-Submit health records to physicians for approval.</p><p>-Follow patient confidentiality/guidelines and legal documentation requirements.</p><p>-Filing and upload transcribed reports.</p><p>-Any other duties as assigned by the management.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>-At least GCE 'N\"/ 'O' Levels, Professional Certificate/ NiTEC, Diploma/ Advanced/ Higher/ Graduate Diploma in any field</p><p>-Related working experience in healthcare and understanding of medical terminology/ abbreviations/ jargon will be an added advantage</p><p>-Strong computer/typing skills. Proficient in MS Office Advantage</p><p>-Meticulous, eye for details, precise, organised and efficient</p><p>-Good communication and interpersonal skill</p><p>-Effective team player and able to work in fast paced environment</p><p>-5.5 days work week (Monday to Friday; Half Saturday)</p><p>-Location: Orchard</p>",
